title: Counter Struck High Definition
description:
Counter-Struck tells the story of a gamer so obsessed with Counter-Strike that his distinction of what is real and what is not slowly fades away.

Chris shot this movie in a local warehouse in Minneapolis MN, for his final project in film class at MCAD. It took about 6 weeks from planning to completion; actual work time (writing, shooting, editing) was about 60-80 hours. It definitely shows, as it turned out simply amazing. This movie is clever and hillarious - definitely a must see.

title: X2 Counter Strike Source Gameplay Movie.
description:
This is my first movie on CS Source, Used a basic program ( Windows Movie Maker ), basically it's just  to show clan's what my level of play is. 

EDIT - 20th March 2010.

First time i've checked this and I lol'd at the comments. First of all I uploaded this when CSS was just a thing I did every now and then with the lads for shits and giggles. Yes I know it's public play and therefore not something a clan should judge too seriously. ( Fyi though this is what helped me get into my first clan, so did the job ). Have been playing CSS though since cs 1.0 casually but only in the last 2-3 years have I been playing competitvley. I use to write for gotfrag.com for the CAL-Euro season 1 ( ChiMeRa ) and have been in a multi tude of clans since this video ( SK187 for example some of the older players may know. ). Currently i've stopped playing games in general to take a break from it.

I'll answer a few questions i've got via comments/pm

Q:Where did you get the track from? 
A: Newgrounds Soundboard, Just remember to ask the owner of the track before using it.

Q: Which program to use if your making a video?
A: This was windows movie maker, very basic and to be honest i'd stick away from it and learn how to use more advanced ones like Adobe Premiere Pro CS4 or Sony Vegas. There are many tutorials out there on the basics. If you want some insane effects i'd also check out video co-pilot if i was you.

Q: What servers do you play on?
A: As i've said i've taken a break from the game, but Nemesis 20 Player Dust2 24/7 server is a great server. All levels of skills play there and you'll always have a laugh.

Video Co-Pilot - http://www.videocopilot.net/
Adobe Prem Pro - http://www.adobe.com/products/premiere/
Sony Vegas - http://www.sonycreativesoftware.com/vegaspro
Vid Tutorials - http://www.enemydown.co.uk/css-movie-making--by-deadcell-article117.php
Nem server IP - 94.23.159.50:27015


GotFrag Writer Archive - http://www.gotfrag.com/css/writers/521951/

When I do come back to CSS, I'll be going back to 5on5's & LAN events, I will no doubt make another movie in the future with far better effects, kills and most importantly no Public footage.

****click more to read the F.A.Q. before posting *****

This is a message to valve saying that their hitbox aren't perfect and actually pretty bad and should be fixed. O and also to all those idiots that post on the comments (99% of people) just try complaining about lag,fps,balistic compensation and you will see how dumb you are~!

To ease my life a bit form dipshits here is the 

Video F.A.Q.:

Q: AM I always right?
A: YES

Q:Its caused by lag r0Fl
A:No! I am on lan. Dickhead

Q:I got it, Its your shit tickrate!
A:No shrelock, its not. Tickrate affect hitbox registry, not hitbox placement

Q:Your computer sucks!
A:No it is better than you will ever be

Q:you only have 25 fps L0lz!!!
A:No! dipshit. I am running fraps on a DEMO! set at 25fps.

Q:Is your comp for real running at -50c
A:yes. Phase change cooling dipshit. go back to grade 10 and learn physics and thermodynamics 

Q:Its because Valve the cock suckers want to make it real and lead the shot! what now biatch? blahblah ballistic compensation
A: Muhahah you suck and failed grade 2math. .338 lapua @ 2700+fps shotting a target 50feet in front of you.running laterally at 10mph max .You sure that aiming 4feet infront is a good idea. DIPSHIT

Q:Am I godly?
A:Yes

Q:are people posting on this video dumb and retarded?
A:Yes

Q:Are you smarter than a 5th grader
A:obviously not.

Q:am I good at cs?
A:cal-p @cs1.6 , cal-i @ cscz. So YES

title: CS:Source - Transparent Spraypaint tutorial
description:
How to make a basic transparent spraypaint image in Photoshop for use in Counter-Strike:Source.

Woo. It turned out really blurry after uploading it :/ Can't even read any of the menu text now :(

Basically what I'm doing here is:

1) Make a new file, 256x256 pixels with a transparent background.

2) Grab a random picture you like and copy/paste it into the new file.

3) Select everything you want to be visible.

4) Click on the "Channels" tab (usually in the same window as your layers) and create a new channel. This will automatically be an alpha channel.

5) Fill your selection with white. Everything that is black on the alpha channel will be considered transparent ingame. Everything that is white will be fully visible, while shades of grey in between will vary the opacity.

6) Now save the file as a 32 bit TGA with alpha channels enabled.

7) Start CS:S and simply import the TGA with the Spraypaint importer and you're done.

title: Counter-Strike 1.5 Gameplay
description:
A movie i made back in 1.5 for my clan.

To answer some questions, there is no "hacks" or cheats in this video, i sped up the video speed by accident when i was collecting hundreds of screenshots inorder to make this video. Yes there is one clip of a member playing vs bots, i didnt have enough recorded footage so i through it in. And yes there is footage from pubs, cal-o (cyber athletic league) matches and pg matches (Proving Grounds League). Remember this video was made in 2002-2003, the core members from this clan eventually played in cal-m and cal-i. My other clan video has footage from a cal-im match if u are intrested. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uon2pZpM_oc

*Had to change the song inorder to keep this video on youtube. old song was lying from you - linking park, new song because of me - seether*

title: Fun Counter-Strike kills video
description:
I made this video when I first started really enjoying playing Counter-Strike 1.6.  It was at the same time that I started to feel like I could actually hold my own on public servers.  I was playing on this server pretty much all the time and decided to make a video of some fun kills and headshots from the demos I had recorded.  Please don't comment saying that I suck or that you are better than me.  I admit that this isn't very impressive but it's meant to be fun to watch, not for me to show off.  I used FRAPS to record the screen and I used Adobe Premiere to edit the videos and soundtrack together.  The songs are both by Stratovarius.  I hope you enjoy the video and are at least entertained if not impressed :-P
You can find out more about this server at kcwarzone.com

title: 4 year old plays Counter Strike
description:
This is my 4 year old. He can pick up just about any game FPS or other "shooter", and play it like a pro. He cannot read, but has learned the menus from watching his older brother and me.  I was shocked at how proficient he has become. This is him skirmishing against a few other guys, it's not his forte', he'd rather play the zombie levels. 

For those who feel the need to post "bad parent" comments, get a life.  There is no evidence that playing this type of game does anything but improve hand eye coordination. My son is a social and academic achiever at the top of his class. He knows the game is pretend. 

To me, this is no different than playing "cops and robbers" with cap guns as I did as a child.

title: Dual Elite Speed Fire in Counter-Strike: Source
description:
Footage of me speed firing the elites in CS:S. The recoil is crazy when I'm not controlling it, 3x greater than the AK47!

****

It's been a while but I guess I should clear this up since there are a lot of idiots on YouTube:

This is not a hack, I simply bound my mouse wheel to attack. I like to use it to burst fire autos and for dualies like I recorded, to do this...

bind mwheelup +attack
bind mwheeldown +attack

Then, roll around on your mouse wheel when you've got the dualies out. Works best if your wheel is smooth when rolling like mine.

Have Fun!

title: Counter-Strike Impossible Dust Bunny Hop
description:
**Update** 11/14/2009
I've disabled comments to address the most commonly asked questions / concerns. 

1.  The bunny hopping is real.  We did not use scripts nor change server settings, etc.  We recorded this footage in Counter-Strike sometime between version 1.0 - 1.6 before bunny hopping got nerfed.

2.  I do not have the song to this video anymore, it was created by my friend while we were in high school and I've since lost the mp3 file.

3.  I do not have the skin-pack that was used in this video either, it's been many years and those files are also long gone.

This was recorded back in my CS'ing days with my good friend, Jake. We were bored, obsessed with bunny-hopping (no hacks) and wanted to see how far we could actually go with it.

After an hour or two of attemping this "Ultimate Dust Hop," Jake actually managed to pull it off. We couldn't believe it so we actually tried again and filmed it. The rest of the video is just goofing around in random public servers.

title: Counter-Strike Source Zombie Mod - Prodigy Flick
description:
EDIT: Since I get so many requests about "How did you do this?!" I'll answer here rather than having to reply individually:

Demo Tool Information can be found at this location:
http://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Demo_Recording_Tools

I just recorded this on a public server. I did not use cheats in any fashion. All that I did was record, follow the player, and used the demo smoother tool to repath the camera (which is why there's all the various camera angles, cutting, etc.), then recorded to avi 2 seperate versions of the scene with a different set of camera angles each. Finally, I used video editing software to cut the pieces together, add the music, and the sound effects. (sound files from Source Engine recordings are almost always out of sync, 85-90% of the time)

There, now the original version of the description:
Here's another CSS test/experiment/gobbalygook thing for you all to chow down on. Here, we have the CSS zombie mod in place on a server. This was taken with an actual player vs. many bot zombies. Note that these zombies are lame and have to use knives. :P

But anyways, did this up fast as possible. Just more fiddling. Fun, good practice. Music from The Ghastly Ones www.ghastlyones.com

title: Amazing Counter Strike Source Movie (Riot 3)
description:
Yes I know the editing isn't that good and there are a lot of things that look bad compared to stuff these days.  Before you comment "editing is bad" (not trying to say it's necessarily good either) just keep in mind most of my videos were made before the days of movie configs and tutorials on how to record, render, and edit.  I didn't have any help, guides, or configs to make things look pretty, so obviously it's not going to look as cool as stuff nearly 5 years after they were made.  Still, I hope you can appreciate them for their time and still enjoy them today.  

Please subscribe to my channel!  

Riot's 3rd video, including highlights of Summer 2007 matches and scrims.  Unfortunately, YouTube only allowed a 100mb limit back in the day, so this is pretty bad quality.  

There are a lot of random shots in here, but they are just that - random and lucky.  I appreciate all your views, ratings, and comments!  Please share this video with your friends!  

Frequently asked questions:

What crosshairscale do you use: I use cl_crosshairscale 2200 on 1650 x 1080 resolution.

What program did you use to make this: I used Sony Vegas to edit the video.

What song is that: All the songs are listed in the credits...

This is a video project I started a year ago, but I was too lazy to finish this (Don't have the scenes anymore, only this preview I once converted).

It's all me playing there, didn't have much HLTV-scenes so I had to use several pub-scenes.

The songs used are:
Enya - May It Be
Linkin Park - Faint
Zeromancer - Dr. Online
A Perfect Circle - Passive

The programs used are:
Half Life - Counterstrike 1.6 (of course :D)
Fraps 2.74 (For capturing the scenes)
Sony Vegas 6.0d (For video editing)
CSE Demoplayer (change preferences of demos)

title: Counter Strike Source 2007-08 " La Pena Negra " 1/2
description:
Conste en acta que no tengo nada contra los wizzard ni las ligas habidas por haber , ni contra pr0s ni nada solo que me parece el Cs:S y sus integrantes, los que van de 
listos, unos jilipoyas que no ven la verdad 35000 personas aprox de las cuales 19000 usan xetos osease 1/2 ó 1/3 pues
hombre dan ganas de hacer un video asi para mentalizar y hacerle ahorrar a alguien 30 euritos mu ricos.

Los que me pongais a parir por este video, aumenta mas vuestra ignorancia, cuando caigais en la conclusion de la verdad
os preguntareis por que tantas horas y para uqe tanto esfuerzo, esto es como la lucha libre...

Muy bonita pero muy teatral a la vez...Una pena negra.

Weno si deseabais saber como hacer o como hacen ciertas personas para usar xetos y que no les pillen... simplemente

echar un vistazo a lo que hay a continuacion :


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=df5pTQAAsOk

http://cheat-project.com/details.php?id=72

p.d: existen ademas xetos comprables que en españa ya suman mas de 10000 que para cuando llegen a los 
19000 como estos tambien hare un video protesta de como alguien se gasta 200 euros en chetos de pago...

En fin esperemos que el Call of Duty 4 y el Crysis dejen a Steam en la Ruina porque la forma en que
todos, y digo todos , porque entre todos podiamos aver hecho algo util por el Cs:S para salvarlo, y hemos dejado
que se arruine como en su dia paso con el quake 3 arena y otrs grandes como unreal...


"Para que esto no pase mas con un juegazo, recordar Cs:S La Pena Negra(detras de Dust 2) como un ejemplo de lo unico que
alguien NO CIEGO ante casi un 50% de españoles, puede hacer en protesta contra este atraco de hackers y xetos
an hecho con un mito como el counter strike...Gracias y Banear xetos a punta pala"

                                           evangelio segun San Hitman El Baneador ScS



Webs de los Mods para que os los descargeis, saber que al instalarlos a de hacerse con steam cerrado y 
poneros la consola con lo de " -console " y poneros vuestros binds o autoexec a gusto personal:


http://www.gamershell.com/download_21825.shtml  http://files.filefront.com/FortressForever11+incremlzip/;8935345;/fileinfo.html *1 Fortress Forever (Mejor que Team Fortress 2 que la han cagado....)
http://www.zombiemaster.org/files.php *2 Zombie Master(Mejor que zombie del Cs:S)
http://games.internode.on.net/filelist.php?filedetails=9069  http://halflife2.filefront.com/file/Perfect_Dark_Source_Client_EXE_Patch;80198 *3 Perfect Dark (Mod Español de españoles que se lo curran...)
http://www.ausgamers.com/files/details/html/27188 *4 Dystopia (Futurista y muy guapo)
http://www.ausgamers.com/files/details/html/27538 *4 Dystopia (Futurista y muy guapo)
http://files.filefront.com/KZmod+full+Beta31+clientexe/;9003729;/fileinfo.html *5 Kreedz Climbing (De escalada y mejor 1000 veces que las xc_ del Cs:S)
http://halflife2.filefront.com/file/HalfLife_2_ExitE_Mod;70107 *6 Exite Alpha Mod
http://files.filefront.com/bg2+11bexe/;9003297;/fileinfo.html *7 The Batlegrounds (U.S.A vs Inglaterra Año 1776 sobra decir mas...)
http://files.filefront.com/DBSourcerar/;7241584;/fileinfo.html  http://www.gamershell.com/news/40519.html *8 Dragon Ball Source (Kamehame....ha...)
http://mods.moddb.com/4832/project-22/downloads/ *9 Project 22 (Mejor que Half Life Deathmatch)

description:
Распрыг с гранатой.

На самом деле это уже очень старое видео, не стоит к нему относится серьёзно... можно только вспомнить те далёкие и весёлые времена , когда еще существовал сотый тикрэйт, в сорсе еще не было ненужных убогих ачивок и статистики нагружающей сервер и клиент, тот весёлый баг, когда убитого в ноги энеми почему то подбрасывало вверх, когда зум у авп включался без задержки после свитча , когда начинаешь одевать глушак на эмку, дропаешь и подбираешь её, а он уже одет...   вспомнили? ...  кто то вспомнил, а кто то эти времена не застал и играет в деревянный, не доделанный  ксго...   жаль... :' \

Commands to get rid of your hud when recording the recorded demos:
sv_cheats 1
hidepanel all
hideradar 1
cl_radaralpha 0
hidepanel specmenu
Hud_saytext_time 0
Hud_centerid 0

title: Silent walk/Russian walking in Counter-Strike 1.6
description:
A form of silent fast walk popularly known as "Russian walking".
Works with mouse wheel bound to +duck and a normal +duck button.

What I am trying to show is the rhytm you have to use in order to make this work. I know it took me some time to find it. :)

My hardware which is in the clip is; logitech G3 mouse, Logitech old keyboard (white wired), big allsop mat and a 17" AOC screen.
I use a resolution of 640*480, powerstrip and net_graph 3

There is no music

In the background there is my boxing sack, snowboard and a kettlebell

title: Counter-Strike: About RATES
description:
I got a request from "anonymous" asking me to make a video about counter-strike 1.6 rates. So I did... I was busy, so I made it quick. 

Usually default rates people in CAL (http://www.caleague.com) use are

Rate 25000
cl_cmdrate 101
cl_updaterate 101
ex_interp 0.01

Those rates are referred as "LAN Rates"

Rates I use since I have comcast could be those rates but instead I use

Rate 20000
cl_cmdrate 100
cl_updaterate 100
ex_interp 0.01

If you need more information about rates go to the following website.

http://guides.freddyshouse.com/cs/tweaking/part2.php

That should help you out a little more.

*Remember rates dont help you shoot better or give you more skill...and it sure isnt hacking because some noobs think that :).

This is part 1 of "Tweaking"

New one coming soon. & Please Rate/Comment/Subscribe/Request.

If you need any strats for some matches I do have some good ones for first round strat. Just message me!

title: Counter Strike 1.6 - How to make a Custom Spray
description:
ENABLE ANNOTATIONS THE LOCATION FOR THE CUSTOM SPRAY HAS CHANGED SINCE THE LATEST 1.6 UPDATES VALVE MADE

In this tutorial I will teach you how to make a custom spray on cs 1.6.

--------------------------------------

You can download HL Tag Converter here:
http://www.mediafire.com/?dujnm2iyc5m

--------------------------------------

If this tutorial helped you please visit http://www.any.gs/d330f70d wait 5 seconds and then click SKIP on the upper right corner. Everytime someone does so I get paid a fraction of a cent that will eventually build up and I get some extra cash to spend :P Want to get paid for links too? Register for free at: http://www.linkbucks.com/referral/313443

--------------------------------------

Whole tutorial in text:

1. Open up HL Tag Converter
2. Select the image you want.
(Must be .BMP, .GIF or .JPG)
3. Adjust Image
4. Save It, Export to WAD File
5. Name it tempdecal.wad and save it on your desktop
6. Open the drive where you have installed CS (C:\ for example)
7. Open Program Files, Steam, steamapps, common, half-life, cstrike
8. Put the tempdecal.wad into your cstrike folder. If you see an old tempdecal.wad file inside remove it first.
9. Right click on the new tempdecal.wad file and select Properties.
10. Check the Read Only box and press ok.
11. Copy the tempdecal.wad file and go back to your counter-strike folder.
12. Paste the tempdecal.wad in any folder that starts with cstrike, eg cstrike_lv.
13. Close the windows and start enjoying your new custom spray :D

--------------------------------------

Counter Strike Global Offensive 2012
Counter Strike Source

Movie (released on 6/15/08)

by K1u

"I enjoyed the whole entire Jaro series and I feel that k1u is a very good producer with a lot to bring to the table. Starting off, the introduction was put together very nicely and it actually set the mood for the rest of the film unlike other movies out there. Leading into the frag sequences, they were put together flawlessly. The song selection was very unique and unlike any that I've heard. The the frags themselves were utterly without a doubt one of a kind. The way that k1u synced up the frags was truly amazing. Throughout the entire movie, the editing was the part that really caught my eye. There were so many effects that I've seen in previous movies, but never in my life have I seen them used in such a fashion which added a great deal to the viewing pleasure. Overall this is one of the best movies to date and I congratulate k1u on making yet again, another successful movie. Two BIG thumbs up from me!" - sMB

title: Change Resolution In Counter Strike
description:
change resolution in counter strike if you can't change it from game.
************UPDATED*********** *:
500 for 1280
400 for 1024
320 for 800
300 for 768
258 for 600
140 for 320

*******WIDESCREEN**********
open your pc calculator and change it to professional calculator. Select "Dec" and write your screen width (e.g. 1400). then select hex and see the number. write this number you got as the width. then repeat it again but now write your screen height (e.g. 1200) and select "hex". you will get the numbers you want to put in regedit..

title: Counter Strike: Source - Low Violence Death Animations
description:
For some reason instead of dying as ragdolls, the characters in my game do this ridiculous animation, and I don't know how to turn it off.

Edit:

Ok, I figured out how to fix it, if any of you are having this problem, or if you feel like playing like this for whatever reason. In your console type these commands:
violence_agibs 1
violence_ablood 1
violence_hgibs 1
violence_hblood 1

replace the ones with zeroes if you WANT these ridiculous animations.

title: The Militia Movie p1. 2002 Counter Strike - CSGoodies.com
description:
This is a VERY CLASSIC old school video!

Comments By Castor_Troy: Being featured on top gaming websites including CS Nation, Domain of Games and the Cyberathlete Professional League, Militia Part 1 was greatly anticipated in the Counter-Strike community from it's birth, and it surely did not disappoint. From the opening scenes, the excitement of the chase was realized. The_Family_God's directorial and editorial skills soared beyond expectations, as a true drama unfolded in only this, Part One of many. Knowing the work involved in creating such a movie, I was pleasantly surprised at both the choreography and quality that this top-notch production presented, as flaws were truly minute. The ambience was quite appropriate and extremely well laid out. I never knew a CS movie could have such a brilliant and in depth plot.
Like the many that have seen this movie, my only remark is that my thirst must be immediately quenched with Part Two. We demand it!
Be sure to expect wonders from this renowned moviemaker. Keep it up Fam!
As Reviewed By Schemer or [dB4d]Face

title: How to start Counter Strike Source dedicated server if srcds.exe doesn`t start...
description:
1. Go to your Counter Strike Source folder...
2. Right click to srcds.exe...
3. Select Properties
4. You can see there `Target`
5. To the end of the line press spacebar then enter `-game cstrike` without ``
6. Press apply then ok

Thats all you need to do... Now start scrds.exe, configure the server... And play :P

title: Noobs in Counter-Strike 1.6 War3FT mod
description:
This is dedicated to every single whining noob there is.

Starring:
 - Woozle# - cowardly whining camper noob
 - ProBe^eon - lazy admin who listens to noobs and doesn't bother to check a thing
 - me

Background:

This is again a video of my playing in Counter-Strike 1.6 with war3 mod. Also this one got me banned.

So, here I am, attempting to point at the ridiculous noobness of the dude, as well as the skill which was mistaken as cheating.

Look at the noob whine after I killed him. "Bohoo, everyone who beats me is a cheater bohoo admins ban him bohoo" he is trying to say with a tear in his eye when he mumbles "oen curasaion 2h+aim". (These noobs always mistype my nick... "Curasion", "Curation", "Cursation"... The list goes forever on.)

Look at the video. After I kill the guy with grenade, keep watching the cliff next to the building. Woozle# camps there with his invisibility (it doesn't mean completely invisible, it means only see-through). He can be clearly seen. I didn't notice him before because I'm simply fucking blind, and didn't look there. And noticing him while he sits cloaked in my sight takes wh? It takes only a trained eye. And then about the kill. Look how long I had him in my screen. When I noticed him you can clearly see how I aim myself. You get your crosshair moving like that only with a bad mouse. The fact I shot him with hs... Well, there's something known as skill. At least you should have some when you've played for years.

Look how I killed the previous guys in that round. It's ridiculous I get called a cheater with such a sloppy playing. Come fucking on...

Guess what I noticed when I watched the complete demo? Last round Woozle# was the only T left, camping somewhere from remaining 4 or 5 CTs... When I was walking outside, he was sitting in the same place. :p

In the first round I played or so, I saw someone (Woozle#) teleport from the T end but didn't know exactly where... Turned out he was on the roof of the building I mainly am in in the video.

description:
This is the second tip in the series. This tip is a segment on The Get Pwned Show. The show is about professional gamers and following them and their careers. It also helps aspiring gamers learn how to get on the path to become a Pro Gamer. All footage was recording during Cevo-PT/Cevo-P Season.

You can check it out at 7 pm East on Thursday at www.highdesertcommunity.com

---------------------------------------

Tip #2 - Headshot Box on De_nuke

This video shows my spot I play in ramp and how you should hold it. It is a common played spot and the trick is not staying there but rotating. Your objective is to protect the LOWER bombsite. The headshot box is temporary and once they push ramp, you must rotate lower and hold from there. Try to take at least one person out before rotating if you can.

Good spots to go after the rotation are window side, big box, or barrel side.

Any questions leave some comments and I will reply.

*UPDATED*

Lessons offered here at my forums:
http://maingearforums.com/showthread.php?t=1932

title: The old Counter-Strike training mission (Part 1)
description:
I bet you didn't know that CS originally came with a training level, did you? Back when the game was first released at retail, Valve made this training level to get players familiarized with CS's core gameplay mechanics. This is something I wish more developers did. Or at least go the Unreal Tournament route and have bots or something.

This training stage appeared only in non-Steam ("WON" by some, referring to the original online service HL games ran on) versions of Counter-Strike. It's in there as late as 1.0.0.5 (CS 1.5), but it's gone in 1.6. It's not really needed as most people have played it, but it's kind of a bummer it's not in there these days.

Hey, Valve! How about a TF2 training level! Wouldn't hurt anything...

title: Developing Homemade Indie games / Counter-Strike in VC++ & DarkGDK
description:
I programmed a 3D application that uses and animates exported objects from the well known game Counter-Strike (CS) (GIGN-mdl  and a bsp map-fy_snow both converted to X). Model contains only animation for running and idle, collision detection not implemented. The low fps from the video is due to the screen recorder.I was thinking in transforming a counter strike game in a RTS based game. I'm waiting for comments or ideas. If you request tutorials,  on how to make game from scratch, please let me know and i'll start a new channel about game development. This is programmed in Visual C++ express 2008 (it was free, i don't know if the download links are still available). You also need the DarkGDK from the game creators site, see links below. If you want to start programming games, i recommend a game creator kit, it's a good way to start to create a game, you can try with VC++ and GDK, because you can find plenty of tutorials and "how to''s and support. 
Going into the indie games development, it's a fun way to start learning programming, much more fun than doing other kind of developer work, it worked for me. If you like my projects, spare a second to subscribe and also visit my other videos, and you can leave comments, i'm always open for suggestions.

DarkGDK page:
http://www.thegamecreators.com/?m=view_product&id=2128

DIYengineering page:
http://leontinatanasoaei.wix.com/diyengineering

https://plus.google.com/+poweredBYGDKDIYengineering/posts

title: koman 1 frag movie counter strike CS pro 1.6 1.7 video clip trailer CAL CEVO
description:
Some of my old CS clips... if you're not familiar with counter-strike 1.6 ... 

Wiki - Counter-Strike is a first-person shooter in which players join either the terrorist or counter-terrorist team (or becomes a spectator). Each team attempts to complete their mission objective and/or eliminate the opposing team. Each round starts with the two teams spawning simultaneously, usually at opposite ends of the map from each other. A player can choose to play as one of eight different default character models (four for each side, although Counter-Strike: Condition Zero added two extra models, bringing the total to ten). Players are generally given a few seconds before the round begins (known as "freeze time") to prepare and buy equipment, during which they cannot attack or walk/move (a player can still take damage, having the player drop from a certain height during freeze time was the only way somebody could control the players starting "HP"). They can return to the buy area within a set amount of time to buy more equipment (some custom maps included neutral "buy zones" that could be used by both teams). Once the round has ended, surviving players retain their equipment for use in the next round; players who were killed begin the next round with the basic default starting equipment.

title: Counter Strike: Source Engine Error Fix
description: Are you getting the "Engine Error Internal driver error in IDirect3DDevice9::Present()" message whenever you try to play css? Here is a fix. Go under the "My Games" tab in steam, and right click "Counter Strike: Source". Click on "Properties", then "Set launch options". Once there, type in "-dxlevel 80". Click "Ok", and your CSS should be working fine. This worked for me.

title: [OPM] Counter Strike In Real Life II 1/2
description:
Sequel parodii Counter-Strike 1.6 w wykonaniu OPM. Tym razem parodia jest bardziej dopracowana, naprawione zostały wszystkie błędy popełnione w pierwszej części, CS In Real Life II ma dużo lepszą jakość, jest bardziej profesjonalnie obrobiony i przede wszystkim zastosowaliśmy w nim wiele nowych elementów, które nie spotykane były do tej pory w ŻADNEJ innej parodii CS'a. Nikt nie może więc tego nazwać odgrzewanym kotletem. Zrobiliśmy wszystko, aby tak nie było. Cały OPM bardzo się postarał. Nagraliśmy to z zamiarem przebicia pierwszej części. Czy nam się to udało? Sprawdźcie sami :D 

PS Wszystkie sytuacje przedstawione w parodii są fikcyjne i wymyślone tylko w celu wywołania śmiechu, a wszelkie wyzwiska itp. mają na celu wierne oddanie klimatu CS'a i kultury polskich graczy ;] Prosimy brać to na luzie :P

title: Counter Strike Source | Smooth Surf Server [HD]
description:
README:

A short tutorial on how to get a smooth surf server in seconds!
with pro settings as well!

I have made two configs to help you:

Server.cfg and Training.cfg:
http://files.filefront.com/13905054

if the download doesn't work, just copy these into a notepad document and call it server.cfg or training.cfg (note: you cannot have both configs in one config file)

server.cfg:

sv_accelerate 5
sv_wateraccelerate 5
sv_wateraccelerate 10
sv_waterfriction 1
sv_friction 4
sv_gravity 800
sv_pushaway_force 30000
sv_unlag 1
sv_maxupdaterate 100
sv_airaccelerate 150
phys_pushscale 1
cl_cmdrate 100
cl_updaterate 100

training.cfg:

sv_accelerate 5
sv_wateraccelerate 5
sv_wateraccelerate 10
sv_waterfriction 1
sv_friction 4
sv_gravity 800
sv_pushaway_force 30000
sv_unlag 1
sv_maxupdaterate 100
sv_airaccelerate 99999999
sv_cheats 1
phys_pushscale 1
cl_cmdrate 100
cl_updaterate 100
ent_remove_all logic_timer
ent_remove_all trigger_hurt

also, remember to have -ticrate 66 in launch options

The Server.cfg is to make your server surf "friendly".
The Training.cfg is to remove the timer on some surf maps. The timer goes on from the round has started, and when the time has run out, everyone in the server will be teleported to jail. The config is also made to prevent health point loss when you fail a stage.

I also have two other channels, if you are interested;

Song covers: www.youtube.com/NozticMusic
COD/CS 1.6 montages: www.youtube.com/n0ztic

song names :dogs can grow beards all over by devil wears prada
and saliva ladies and gentlemen
 Game play

Counter-Strike: Source inherits characteristics from both Half-Life 2, through the look and feel conveyed through textures and movement, and its predecessor, Counter-Strike 1.6, maintaining the game play style of its predecessor. The basic game play of two teams, terrorists and counter-terrorists, squaring off against each other in a series of rounds in which each team must either complete their objective or eliminate the opposition, has remained unchanged. The two most common types of objectives are bombing and hostages. In competitive play, only maps with bombing objectives are used, since the AI of the hostages has not been improved over previous iterations, and is prone to a number of problems. The weapon recoil has been modified since its predecessor, and is noticeably different from that experienced in Counter-Strike 1.6[1]. In addition, flash bang grenades have been visually modified to take advantage of the Source Engine, and are typically more powerful and effective than in previous games.

Customization

Because of the large fan-base that Counter-Strike: Source has accumulated, there are a wide variety of different customizations and add-ons that can be used with the game. There is a large fanbase for the game that creates customized sounds, textures, weapon skins, and player skins. title: Counter-Struck - By Saturday Night Special Productions
description:
Uploader's Note: I do not claim this video mine. This video is about a gamer playing Counter-Strike and the game becomes a reality. Really funny content. Enjoy!

FilePlanet's Description: 
This is a live-action movie about an obsessed Counter-Strike player who loses his distinction between reality and CS, fighting terrorists on an exciting hostage rescue mission, ending with a clever twist.
Counter-Struck tells the story of a gamer so obsessed with Counter-Strike that his distinction of what is real and what is not slowly fades away. Cleverly playing upon several quirks from the game, this movie follows the Player through his adventures of fighting terrorists and rescuing hostages, and ends with a twist. Chris shot this movie in a local warehouse in Minneapolis MN, for his final project in film class at MCAD. It took about 6 weeks from planning to completion; actual work time (writing, shooting, editing) was about 60-80 hours. It definitely shows, as it turned out simply amazing. This movie is clever and hillarious - definitely a must see. 

Video Description:
Title: Counter-Struck
Released: Jun 6, 2005
Runtime: 00:07:15
Counter-Struck is a parody of the videogame Counter-Strike.
This is the original version of the smash-hit Counter-Struck, released in June of 2005. It was created as Chris Hedeen's final project for Intro to Film class at the Minneapolis College of Art and Design, where he goes to college. 
Counter-Struck made it into the April 2006 issue of Computer Gaming World Magazine, issue 261! Click the magazine cover below to read the interview with Chris!

description:
Produced by Pangea Movies

by Jinxed
"The thing that stands out to me most in this film besides the content is the inclusion of high quality LAN video content which really flows nicely throughout the film. mTw is a team that has done well recently and this film accents some of the obstacles they had to overcome. Overall this is a solid film from start to finish, and a great example of what sophomore producer MaLaK has to offer."

title: Counter-Strike 1.6 pro playing - g1k (no pubs)
description:
A pretty old movie of mine, a couple years ago I made a team with some real life friends called "Internet Explorers", we joined cal-o, lost our first match, and then i dragged the team to be undefeated for the rest of the season to qualify for the next league. The movie highlights some good shots from matches/scrims.

I started playing in 2001 when it was CS 1.3 - but I only started playing competitively way later, CAL season 12 or so. Most of these clips are from CAL-o season 16 when we moved up to CAL-im after. I've played countless times with CAL-m teams against CAL-p players and some CAL-i pugs... but honestly I had the most fun playing with real friends in CAL-o and it was a damn accomplishment when I carried the team through unbeaten 7 match streak to the playoffs. So I was like LeBron James for them! Crazy shit. The match on de_train (the one where I ace and defuse, killing first guy with a pump) we were 15-10 down (it's up to 16). Everyone started whining that we were gonna lose, but I went LeBron James on them, winning the rest of the rounds to tie at 15-15, and then win in triple OT! Oh man, what an emotional video game that was.

I do feel sorry for the dudes that play for 3D , complexity, SK swedent, etc....  holy shit man, Spawn, Frod, Heaton, Potti, Ksharp, Rambo, Bullseye, Shaguar, i0nz, walle... man these people play CS for 7 hours a day... at least! I mean, I understand they get paid like $2000 a month... and win a $60k tournament once in a while that they have to split 10 ways.... but damn, that's some hardcore stuff. I hope these people have a backup, cuz CS ain't gonna last forever.... but then i guess there is cs:source... and HALO... I'm surprised fatal1ty hasn't taken his Quake skillz to the modern games.

title: Counter-Strike 1.6 Movie
description:
A short counter-strike infiltration story which takes place on the Counter-Strike: Condition Zero's de_dust map using Counter-Strike 1.6.

Note: This is Counter-Strike 1.6, but it has the Condition Zero's map and new skins and sounds for the players.

Story:
A few C.T's volunteer to elimate the ground terrorist group's base who have created harvoc and chaos over a long period of time. This group has been professionally trained and follow orders at all costs. This group is under control by the 'commander' who has lots of power and money to spare. He has control of many terrorist groups, this one being the weakest one. And so, he and his assisstant ( Nasu) flee the scene before T.C.T.T's backup arrives. ( As you notice when the C.T's shoot randomly in 3:06 - 3:08 )

This is the first video I have ever made with Counter-Strike :S

description:
First of all, if you don't like the music, turn your volume off (´・ω・`)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Now I'll give you the list of the commands that has been used.
And a bit information about what they do.

sv_cheats 2:
Needed for some of the commands.

r_shadowids 1
moving numbers on screen showing players shadows

mat_wireframe 3
See through walls

sv_showimpacts
Puts a square where bullets hit. Very useful for learning how to control sprays. 
Sv_cheats is not required.
sv_showimpacts 1: shows marks in 2 colors.
sv_showimpacts 2: shows marks in red.
sv_showimpacts 3: shows marks in blue.
sv_showimpacts 0: disables the marks.

r_drawothermodels 2

Now get online and get playing!

Fair use is a use permitted by copyright statute that might otherwise be infringing. Non-profit, educational or personal use tips the balance in favor of fair use.

BTW ask any questions and I'll answer them;


Q1.'When you are playing as a zombie why are your arms still look human?'

A1: Thanks to eNLivEx for the awnser to this. It seems that to show the textures for the zombie arms from an first person view you need to put specific files in a certain location, and the server won't do that for you. It's no real biggie anyway.

Q2.'Why are the zombies all ALIENS from ALIEN VS PREDATOR?'

A2: Because unlike other servers, that use many skins, such as L4D, Fallout 3 and Half-Life, sC just uses the one, which proves to be more popular and successful. I think it's better as well. Seeing a horde of ALIENS if definitively more unsettling than a random assortment of unrelated monsters from different genres of video games.


Q3.'Why don't the zombies have guns?'

A3: (-_-)

title: WCG Polacy mistrzami świata w Counter-Strike
description:
Reprezentacja Polski w grę Counter-Strike zdobyła złoty medal podczas Światowego Finału olimpiady World Cyber Games. Polacy w finałowym pojedynku pokonali szwedzki zespół fnatic. Główną nagrodą dla naszych graczy było 35 tys. dolarów. Tegoroczne WCG przyniosło również sukces indywidualny polskiego zawodnika - Piotr "Pio" Zajkowski zdobył brązowy medal w FIFA 09.

Światowy finał World Cyber Games w Chengdu (Chiny) już za nami. Impreza zakończyła się spektakularnym sukcesem Polaków. Pierwszego dnia zawodów brązowy medal w FIFA 09 zgarnął Piotr "Pio" Zajkowski. Wczoraj najwyższe miejsce na podium zajęła drużyna AGAiN w Counter-Strike.

Niewątpliwie najbardziej prestiżowym zwycięstwem podczas tegorocznego WCG był sukces drużyny AGAiN grającej w Counter-Strike'a. W składzie zespołu znaleźli się gracze doskonale znani z międzynarodowej sceny e-sportowej: Filip "Neo" Kubski, Łukasz "LUq" Wnęk - Counter Strike, Wiktor "TaZ" Wojtas, Jakub "Kuben" Gurczyński oraz Mariusz "Loord" Cybulski.

Drużyna AGAiN w finałowym pojedynku zmierzyła się z utytułowanym szwedzkim zespołem fnatic. Spotkanie było niezwykle zaciekłe i trwało aż trzy godziny, co jest jednym z dłuższych wyników w historii WCG. Ostatecznie, po kilku dogrywkach na obu mapach, Polakom udało się wygrać spotkanie. Za I miejsce nasi zwycięzcy otrzymali 35 tys. dolarów w gotówce oraz ponad 2 tys. dolarów w nagrodach rzeczowych.

Medal przywiózł z WCG również Piotr "Pio" Zajkowski, który zdobył trzecie miejsce w grze FIFA 09.

World Cyber Games (WCG) to największy na świecie turniej gier komputerowych. Organizowany od 2000 r., w świecie e-sportowym postrzegany jest jako odpowiednik Igrzysk Olimpijskich. Sponsorem Światowym WCG jest firma Samsung Electronics. Sponsorami Reprezentacji Polski jest Netia oraz R20 produkująca napoje energetyczne

Wiktor "TaZ" Wojtas
Jakub "kuben" Gurczyński
Filip "Neo" Kubski
Łukasz "LUq" Wnęk
Mariusz "Loord" Cybulski

description:
While others are preparing for CAL and stuff, I was having some fun on some random Jailbreak server playing Simon says or get shot. Usually the last person to do a "last reaction" or someone who does something when he didn't say "Simon" dies. Usually me though. Sometimes the prisoners rebel and we kill the guards.
It really stinks when someone who can't speak clear English through the integrated VoIP is talking. This is why I use Mumble over Teamspeak and Ventrilo.

I later discovered who runs the server and I'm not going back.

This video will come in two parts due to some 10 minute limit.

title: Episode 2 - HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks - The Terrorist weapons
description:
QPAD, the Swedish company famed for its premium gaming gear, today announced the release of a video series of Counter-Strike tips & tricks starring Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen. The series is called "HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks"

Emil "HeatoN" Christensen is a legend throughout the world for his achievements in the Counter-Strike 1.6 pro gaming arena, and his unique technique when shooting. By taking his team "NiP" (Ninjas in Pyjamas) to winning the World Championship and once more with the successful team SK-Gaming, HeatoN has been a centre figure in the pro-gaming arena for a long time. After retiring as an active pro gamer he became General Manager for the Swedish team "Stockholm Magnetik" in the global gaming tournament CGS.

Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen has won several tournaments around the world e.g. 9 CPL, 4 CPL World Championships, 1 World Cyber Games and 3 Nations cups and several other tournaments. Today Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen is making a living out of developing gaming products with several brands. Heaton recently launched his first gaming mouse pad together with QPAD.

The "HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks" series is targeting gamers who like to know the secrets behind HeatoN's success and for gamers who like to improve their skill in Counter-Strike. The rest of the episodes are being launched every second Friday in January and February 2010 on www.facebook.com/QPADse. Starting with Episode 1 "Introduction" and episode 2 "The terrorist weapons" already on December the 22nd just in time before Christmas.

Launch plan
1. Introduction - 22 December 
2. The Terrorist weapons - 22 December 
3. Flash and smoke - 15 January 
4. The Counter Terrorist weapon - 29 January 
5. Wallbanging - 12 February 
6. Config and gear - 26 February
7. Tactic - 12 Mars

title: Counter Strike Source weapons in Left 4 Dead 2 (A rifle, two snipers, one sub machine gun)
description:
The title says it all. I was sniffing around in the cheats and discovered 4 weapons that don't show up in game and i do not recall seeing these weapons before when i was cheatin' around. I haven't seen anyone else reporting these weapons so I thought I'd share them here. I have absolutely no mods with l4d2, never have, so I know I'm not mistaken here when I say that these weapons aren't from a mod. I don't own the game CSS - counter strike source so these came with L4D2 completely stand-alone. 

NOTE: WEAPONS DO NO DAMAGE TO ZOMBIES, HOWEVER ARE FULLY ANIMATED.
Eg: You can shoot them, reload, aim, and blood spatter shows up on zombie's bodies but absolutely zero damage done. Note, errors received when giving these weapons to yourself through cheats. Late Precache error. 

Details in ordered by demonstration in video:

First gun:
Smg: MP5
50 round magazines @ 700 rounds total.
Note: Fully auto gun however, being a player of the modern warfare series, I use the three round burst method of firing.

Second Gun:
Rifle: SG 552 Commando by SIG ARMS inc.
50 round magazines @ 410 rounds total.
Note: Fully auto gun however, being a player of the modern warfare series, I use the three round burst method of firing.

Third Gun:
Sniper, "AWG"
I can't confirm this weapon's true information, maybe a gun expert can.
20 round magazines @ 200 rounds total.
Note: Bolt Action (Fully Animated)

Fourth Gun
Sniper, "Scout"
Same as above, i can't confirm this weapon, perhaps a gun expert can.
15 round magazines @ 195 rounds total.
Note: Bolt-Action (Fully Animated)

If anyone discovers the type of guns the two snipers are, let me know. I'll add information to this video.

description:
Everyone dies.  A single Gun-Game Round.

Music: Both songs were taken from youtube videos.
 0:00 - 1:00 LoniXX-Crazy Train (Remix) -------this user deleted his account.
1:01 - end http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7vuyRpne5V0

Hey, this is my second "Gungame Madness" video.  I wanted to do a little more creative editing on this one than I did for my last, hope you think its interesting.  I haven't played CSS in quite a while, but whenever I do, I record a demo.  This is the first gungame I've played since my last video - Its a bit like riding a bike I believe.  

If you've never played a gungame, read this description to know what's going on:  A gungame is a game where a player moves from one gun to another by killing a certain number of people. In this case, you are supposed to kill two people in order to move to the next weapon. Once you reach level 22, you get a grenade and a deagle, once you get one grenade kill, you get only a knife, and the first one to knife anyone on level 23 wins.

title: Episode 7 - HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks - Tactic
description:
Tactics
For a team to be successful in this day and age it requires a solid strategy going in to each round of play. No matter how good a strategy is without tactical precision it is destined to fail. A well placed and perfectly timed flash bang or grenade can be the difference in a win or a loss. This tactical precision can be much easier to accomplish with the proper mouse, mousepad and headset. Practice is always a major factor in performance but without the proper gear tactical precision can be much more difficult to achieve.

HeatoN Tips & Tricks
The "HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks" series is targeting gamers who like to know the secrets behind HeatoN's success and for gamers who like to improve their skill in Counter-Strike. This is the final episode of season one. To find out more about upcomming seasons, make content requests and post your comments and feedback, subscribe to QPAD channel on YouTube www.youtube.com/QPADse 

About Heaton:
Emil "HeatoN" Christensen is a legend throughout the world for his achievements in the Counter-Strike 1.6 pro gaming arena, and his unique technique when shooting. By taking his team "NiP" (Ninjas in Pyjamas) to winning the World Championship and once more with the successful team SK-Gaming, HeatoN has been a centre figure in the pro-gaming arena for a long time. After retiring as an active pro gamer he became General Manager for the Swedish team "Stockholm Magnetik" in the global gaming tournament CGS. 

Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen has won several tournaments around the world e.g. 9 CPL, 4 CPL World Championships, 1 World Cyber Games and 3 Nations cups and several other tournaments. Today Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen is making a living out of developing gaming products with several brands. Heaton recently launched his first gaming mouse pad together with QPAD.

Launch plan:

2. The Terrorist weapons - 22 December 
3. Flash and smoke - 15 January 
4. The Counter Terrorist weapon - 29 January 
5. Wallbanging - 12 February

title: Counter-Strike: Source - FN F2000
description:
Counter-Strike Source: Modern Warfare 2

FN F2000 Assault Rifle & Desert Eagle Pistol
_____________________________________
Credits:

Animations: .eXe & IW
Compile: Pecks
_____________________________________

The F2000 is a modular weapon system; its principal component is a compact 5.56x45mm NATO-caliber assault rifle configured in a bullpup layout. The F2000 is a selective fire weapon operating from a closed bolt.

The rifle consists of two main assemblies: the barreled receiver group and the frame, coupled together by means of an axis pin located above the trigger guard. The barrel group has an integral MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail used to mount optical sights. The frame or lower receiver contains the trigger group, the bolt and bolt carrier assembly, return mechanism and magazine well. A removable handguard is installed in front of the trigger which completes and encloses the trigger guard.

Counter-Strike Source: ACR
__________________________

Counter-Strike Souce Modern Warfare 2
__________________________

Call of Duty 6: Modern Warfare ACR
http://i802.photobucket.com/albums/yy304/blitzane/acr.jpg
__________________________

The Bushmaster Adaptive Combat Rifle (ACR) is the production name for an updated version of the Masada Adaptive Combat Weapon System. In late January 2008, Bushmaster entered into a licensing agreement with Magpul whereby Bushmaster would take over production, future development and sales of the Masada. It is a patent pending self-loading rifle platform designed by Magpul Industries of Erie, Colorado. The rifle was initially developed over a period of four months, completely independent of government funding. Prototypes were displayed at the 2007 SHOT Show in Orlando, Florida. Originally scheduled for release in the second quarter of 2008, Bushmaster announced on May 16, 2008, that the consumer release would be delayed until Q1 2009, due to a focus on military projects. On November 18, 2008, Bushmaster released a statement saying, "The ACR is being redesigned to be a superior offering to compete for the next generation US Army infantry carbine and subcompact weapon requirement and will be available to select customers in 2009." The ACR was one of the weapons displayed to U.S. Army officials during an invitation-only Industry Day on November 13, 2008. The goal of the Industry Day was to review current carbine technology prior to writing formal requirements for a future replacement for the M4 Carbine.

You can shoot while having that "shield" on

It's a glitch that its as if you're holding your pistol, but your shield is glitched so that it remains there when ure using your primary weapon. Come and get Fragged! TFL & INTEL team up for Massive $25,000 Computer Games Competition at 
The Primrose Best Western Hotel in Toronto August 20-21st 2005 Monday August 8th - For immediate
release Toronto, August 8th  Toronto Fun League LTD (TFL) are pleased to announce the details of
Torontos most-awaited BYOC (Bring-Your-Own-Computer) event by hardcore and professional
gamers. The Intel TFL Summer Fragfest 2005 will be held at the Primrose Best Western Hotel on Saturday
 and Sunday August 20-21st 2005. 

The Intel TFL Summer Fragfest 2005 will feature professional tournaments ranging from the ever-popular

title: Team 3D G4 Counter-Strike Frag Movie
description:
This is a short frag movie made by none other then David Cho (DchozN)

This movie actually aired on G4 a few years back.

all credit to David cho - more info on movie below (the readme)

Brennan,

Thank you for this great opportunity, and making everything happen for us, Team 3D.  I wish you the best of luck at G4, which honestly is a badass and remarkable job at such an early stage in your life.  Very fortunate and grateful our paths have crossed so to speak, and you've caught me at an incredibly busy week with some truly amazing opportunities (I will tell you more about this later).  Thank you for your kind words towards my work for the past year or so, and thank you again.

As far as the video is concerned, I did what I could in a day and given the time constraints, this is my best work.  I've edited out the violence and gore out of the game, achieved a music video look and feel, constant motion, high production values, editing, featured Team 3D (the loss of the logos and such is not that big of a deal), utilized the audio track you gave me from APM, kept it under 1 minute and 30 seconds for the running time, and rendered it best I could (extreme high quality with WMV9 at 800x600 resolution, 29 NTSC FPS framerate, and MP3 320 KBPS encoded audio).  I'm sure I missed out a few areas and matters I wanted to mention and discuss (most are pretty trivial I guess and not absolutely important), but all that matters is I've finished a video, which I'm extremely proud of, for G4 that will hopefully be aired thanks to you (it's 4:03 A.M. CST right now - can't think and remember properly ;o).  I believe if everything goes well this will be the first time Counter-Strike team skill/frag orientated video will be aired on TV.  If you can message me as soon as possible if this will be aired and the date and time so I may write a news piece for it on Team3D.com (and possibly other major electronic sports websites), and give you the proper credits of course.  I have a feeling that I missed mentioning some thing(s), but the video is finished and ready to go and that's all that matters, really.  I'd like to thank you once again, and definitely keep in touch.

Regards,

David Cho

DchozN@DchozN.com
DCho@GotFrag.com

title: Counter Strike Base Builder Gameplay
description:
The "Base Builder Mod" is a special zombie mod. The big difference is, that you have to build the bases where you can hide from the zombies, by yourself. 

How to bind a key:
You have to bind a key first. Write "bind key +grab" in the console to bind a key. The key is a letter, for example "o".
You have to say "bind o +grab" to bind o as key (don´t write the " ). Now look at a block and press the key. Now you should be able to move the block around.  

Edit:
When I made this video I didn´t know that I also can use the mouse. 

I played on the "Basebuilder Mod" on the Server 
"NeonDragon.net CS5 Base Builder" 

178.32.59.1:27022

Hou can find the server-rules here:
http://neondragon.forumotion.co.uk/neondragonnet-cs5-base-builder-f80/base-builder-server-rules-t5450.htm

P.S. This is not an official advertisement video or something like that.
The rules or the gameplay on other servers can differ.

title: Wie mache ich mein Counter Strike Source nach dem Update wieder uncut?
description:
Hallo Leute. Ich hab diesen Trick zwar vor 3 Monaten angewender, aber das habe ich von Valve persöhnlich, weil ich denen ein Steam Support Ticket geschrieben habe. Hier ein Ausschnitt:

Bitte befolgen Sie diese Schritte, um die richtige Version dieses Spiels zu erhalten: 1.Klicken Sie auf Windows START  AUSFÜHREN  tippen Sie regedit und drücken Sie die Eingabetaste 2. Bitte wählen Sie im folgenden Dialog die Suchfunktion und suchen Sie nach: \HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\VALVE Löschen Sie bitte diesen Verzeichnisstamm in Ihrer Registry. Starten Sie nun Steam neu und starten Sie Ihr Spiel.

Hoffe das hilft nun hier.

Achtung: Das klappt nur wenn ihr euer CS auch uncut gekauft habt

Musik: These new Puritans - We want war

description:
ItsMods: http://www.itsmods.com/forum/member.php?action=register&referrer=624
Twitter: http://twitter.com/Azumikkel


Counter-Strike: Warfare:
-You start with ?? credits (Default: 800)
-You get credits for killing.
-Buy weapons from the buymenu using these. Most weapons included are included in Counter-Strike as well.
-Miscellaneous submenu to buy stuff such as frags, flashes, ammo and armor.

-You have 1 primary and 1 handgun.
-You start with an USP 45.
-Right-clicking (aiming) with USP, M9 or M4A1 makes you put a silencer on it, just like in CSS.
-Aiming down sight has been disabled for all weapons except for snipers, bullpup (aug w/ acog) and krieg 552 (fal w/ acog).
-Bullet spread has been decreased as well as the crosshair size in addition to the disabled ADS.
-Everyone starts with double hp and no health regeneration. Hp counter shows only half of it though (+ 100)
-You cannot sprint, in addition you walk faster to match the speed of CSS
-Headshots and intervention are one-shot kills (unless the enemy bought armor)

Admin submenu included (for host and admins, specified in the mod):
(May have added/removed some to prevent host advantage before release)

=== +100 HP

=== TOGGLE UNLIMITED CREDITS FOR ALL

title: Episode 5 - HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks - Wallbanging
description:
HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks - Episode 3 - Flash and smoke

QPAD, the Swedish company famed for its premium gaming gear, today announced the release of the third episode of the video series of Counter-Strike tips & tricks starring Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen. The latest episode is called "HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks Flash and Smoke"

The "HeatoN Counter-Strike Tips & Tricks" series is targeting gamers who like to know the secrets behind HeatoN's success and for gamers who like to improve their skill in Counter-Strike. The rest of the episodes are being launched every second Friday during January and February 2010. Episode 3 includes a smoke trick used by HeatoN versus element in the CPL final 2003.

Emil "HeatoN" Christensen is a legend throughout the world for his achievements in the Counter-Strike 1.6 pro gaming arena, and his unique technique when shooting. By taking his team "NiP" (Ninjas in Pyjamas) to winning the World Championship and once more with the successful team SK-Gaming, HeatoN has been a centre figure in the pro-gaming arena for a long time. After retiring as an active pro gamer he became General Manager for the Swedish team "Stockholm Magnetik" in the global gaming tournament CGS.

Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen has won several tournaments around the world e.g. 9 CPL, 4 CPL World Championships, 1 World Cyber Games and 3 Nations cups and several other tournaments. Today Emil "HeatoN" Christenssen is making a living out of developing gaming products with several brands. Heaton recently launched his first gaming mouse pad together with QPAD.

Launch plan:
1. Introduction - 22 December
2. The Terrorist weapons - 22 December
3. Flash and smoke - 15 January
4. The Counter Terrorist weapon - 29 January
5. Wallbanging - 12 February
6. Config and gear - 26 February
7. Tactic - 12 Mars

About QPAD:
QPAD built its success on a grassroots commitment to the gaming community. Like you, we thrive in the madness of competition and embrace the free spirit of gaming. Our sponsorship of the QTOUR, communities, cups, tournaments, teams and LAN parties reflects this commitment. The knowledge weve gained has fed into our development of high quality products that have a great performance and given many a winning edge. For more information on QPAD, visit the official website: www.qpad.se

title: Counter strike source Hammer Editor making a simple cube map and player spawns [Greek-tutorial]
description:
Αποφάσισα να ανεβάσω βιντεάκια tutoria για όσους ενδιαφέρονται να μάθουν σχετικά με Counter strike sourse map making.Με λίγα λόγια θέλουν να μάθουν 
να φτιάχνουν CSS maps.Δεν τα ξέρω όλλα για αύτο θα προσπαθήσω να σας εξηγήσω όσο πιο αναλυτικά ότι ξερω χρησημοποιώντας την Ελληνικη γλώσσα για να σπάσω αυτή την μονοτονία των tutorials :P.

Αυτό το βίντεο περιγράφει πως να φτιάξετε έναν απλό map με μορφή κουτιού καθώς και player spawn.Subscribe άμα θέλετε δεν ειναι αυτός ο σκοπός μου πάντος άλλα για να μην πω ψέματα δεν θα με χάλαγε.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Πρεπει να γνωρίζετε ότι:

Ο map  που έφτιαξα χωράει μέχρι δυο παίχτες ένα ct και ένα t.Αν θέλετε map πχ 10 παιχτών θα πρέπει να φτιάξετε 5 ct entities kai πέντε t entities αντί μία και μία.Και για να μήν χάνετε χρόνο πατήστε ctrl+c (copie)και μετά ctrl+v (paste) σε κάποιο σημείο του χάρτη για να μην τρώτε χρόνο ένα ένα.
Θα πρέπει πάντα όμως να είναι ίσες οι αναλογίες ποτέ τέσσερεις ct και  πέντε t .Aλιώς ο map δεν θα λειτουργεί σωστά.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Για τυχόν απορίες γράψτε comet και θα προσπαθήσω να 
απαντήσω το σηντομότερο.
Αργότερα εφόσον ανεβάσω και τα άλλα tutorial θα δοθεί και διεύθυνση email.

title: My Counter-Strike:Source - map: fy_rocketyard
description:
This map is based off the iceworld map from both the original Counter-Strike and the Counter-Strike: Source version. Its a simple 8vs8, 16 in all, Fight Yard map. You have all CS weapons sprawled out in each spawning zone. The CT's have the T's weapons as well as their own and the T's have the CT's weapons along with their own, so every gun is essentially available to every player. A single He-grenade is placed in the middle of the map and eight additional He-grenades can be found in two opposite corner pockets of the map. There is also a weapons depot down on the lower level(this houses the depot only and serves as nothing more then just my in-game credits. If you can't, for some reason, find it or wanna quickly locate it then just look around for that weird orangish looking square that seems to be visible no matter what angle or object you are behind. The depot has, I believe like, five or six different rifles, with at least three of each one, there are also three Tmp's and three Degale's. With even more He-grenades and the only area that has Flashbangs, and Smoke Grenades. The C4, Defusal Kits, ammo boxes, food bags and the RPG's are all just for looks. Sorry I wish they weren't but I'm not really that good of a mapper...yet=)

   The maps theme is set in a wintry forest some where out in an undisclosed location. Due to the fact that this is an ICBM missile testing facility the reasons for which it is in an isolated and undisclosed location should be quite obvious. This map is purely fictional and I used no references other then what I've seen on the History Channel or like wise on the Military Channel so no I don't know where this place is and I've surely never seen/heard/or want to go there. 

Thanks for watching this video preview for my latest CS:S map: "fy_rocketyard."

This, as with all my maps, will be made available via: http://www.fpsbanana.com/games/2 

While a few other maps of mine can also be found at: 
http://www.moddb.com/members/usimc

./hldsupdatetool.bin

och om du vill kan du ändra port med kommandot: -port XXXX

title: Counter Strike: Source (CS:S) - Deutschland vs. Dänemark - Teil 1
description:
Wisst ihr noch was ich letzte Woche gesagt habe?: "Ein noch mehr epischen Match, als das hier, geht zurzeit wirklich nicht!" - Balkespower 13.11.2010, mTw vs. Sk Gaming (1/4)... 
Nun.... 

ES GEHT NOCH EINE STUFE EPISCHER!!!

Und zwar mit diesem alten Länderspiel hier (was ich gesucht und gefunden hab): Deutschland vs. Dänemark aus der ASUS.ENC (Das ist das, was für die Fußball-Fans die Fußball-EM ist :P) mit den besten der Besten Spieler aus der deutschen und dänischen CS:S Pro Series!!!

Dieses Spiel ist so krass und geil geworden und daher zu schade, um zu sagen, wie viele Teile es insgesamt gibt, weil dieser Match sonst ziemlich gespoilert würde, wenn ich das tue!

Daher hab ich mir einen Spaß erlaubt: Ich sag euch nur, welcher Teil es ist, um euch wenigsten eine Orientierung zu geben. Wenn euch diese Idee gefällt und es auch bei den normalen Matches haben wollt, sagt es mir ruhig.

PS: In Mase wird der Patriot in ihm entfacht!!!

Anzahl der Maps auf denen gespielt wird: Max. 3
Map: de_inferno

Besondere Regelung bei solchen Matches:
- Es wird "the best of three" gespielt, das heißt, dass ein Team zwei Maps von drei gewinnen muss, um das Match zu gewinnen.
- Es gibt nur Win/Loss pro Map, das heißt es gibt keine Unentschieden pro Map, entweder man gewinnt oder verliert die Map!!
- Falls es doch zu einem Unterschieden (15:15) kommen sollte, wird "Overtime", sprich 10 zusätzliche Runden (5 pro Hälfte und einem Startgeld von 10000$), gespielt und wenn das auch in einem Untentschieden resultiert wird einfach wieder "Overtime" usw. gespielt bis ein Team gewinnt.

Grundregeln (für die, die es nicht kennen :P):
-Gespielt wird 5vs5
-Gespielt wird nur auf Defuse Maps (de_......)
-Auf jede Map werden zwei Hälften á 15 Runden gespielt (min.16 Runden max. 30 Runden) (ungefähr wie beim Fußball) :P
-Der Sieger beim Knife Round (am Anfang) kann die Seite wählen (T o. CT) und nach 15 Runden wechseln die team´s die Seiten
-Das Team das 16 Punkten erzielt gewinnt die Map bzw. hat dann das Match gewonnen, wenn es sich um die letzte Map handelt bzw. nur auf einer Map gespielt wird

Have BIG Fun (und Ausdauer!) beim anschauen!!! :)

title: Loquendo: como poner musica en el Counter Strike 1.6
description:
Aqui el link del rar:

http://www.mediafire.com/?22sjvuzzhxhug57

Y los binds para poner en el cs :D !:

bind "KP_MINUS" "voice_inputfromfile 1; voice_loopback 1; +voicerecord"
bind "KP_PLUS" "voice_inputfromfile 0; voice_loopback 0; -voicerecord"

Serían estas teclas
http://cloud6.lbox.me/images/384x384/201307/g300-usb-pc-keyboard-game-con-104-teclas-mate-para-pc-laptop-notebook_hmknvv1373612204588.jpg

Ej: 

Recuerden, es mi primer video y perdonen que se me olvido poner el puntero xDDD!!
Recuerden, comenten y puntuen :D !! xD


Ps. Si usan notebook compacto cambien los binds a otro qe les acomode, ej:

bind "f1" "voice_inputfromfile 1; voice_loopback 1; +voicerecord"    Para poner el sonido

bind "f2" "voice_inputfromfile 0; voice_loopback 0; -voicerecord" Para parar el sonido, si no lo apretan no podran hablar por microfono

Pss: Que no se los olvide antes de abrir el cs apretar en la manito con el pulgar arriba!

Psss. Ahora, no funciona directamente el Convert to, ya que no eh encontrado el keygen o crack para el programa , ahora tienen que hacer click en el icono, seleccionan los sonidos y funciona igualmente ;)

title: Counter-Strike Source GamePlay Online [HD] By rflfn STEAM_0:0:23419527
description:
GamePlay Online  em servers 4FUN do game Counter-Strike Source, o melhor Game de FPS Online de todos os tempos.

Informações:
Gravei as demos primeiro, depois retirei as partes que eu queria com o Fraps, e depois editei e coloquei os efeitos com o Sony Vegas Pro.

Quem gostou e quiser fazer o mesmo recomendo usar os comandos a seguir no console antes de gravar com o Fraps quando estiver assistindo as demos:


Para desabilitar tudo:

hud_saytext_time 0 // retira os textos do chat.
voice_enable 0 // retira as vozes dos outros jogadores.
net_graph 0 // retira a janela que mostra o FPS
hideradar 1 // retira o radar


Para habilitar novamente:

hud_saytext_time 12 // habilita novamente os textos.
voice_enable 1 // habilita novamente as vozes dos outros jogadores.
net_graph 1 // habilita a janela que mostra o FPS.
drawradar // habilita novamente o radar.

title: Как создать Counter Strike 1.6 сервер [100% работоспособность]
description:
Привет.
Сегодня я научу тебя  делать  быстро и качественно Counter Strike 1.6 сервер.

1 Шаг.
Создаем папку в D диске и называем Server
Скачиваем HLDS Update Tool 
Устанавливаем HLDS Update Tool  в папку Server.

2 Шаг.
Запускаем CMD.
Прописываем эти строчки:
D:\Server\HldsUpdateTool.exe -command update -game valve -dir D:\Server

4 Шаг.
Прописываем эти строчки:
D:\Server\HldsUpdateTool.exe -command update -game cstrike -dir D:\Server

5 Шаг.
Скачиваем Admin Pack - http://www.mediafire.com/?y5c950i9wanyfww
Устанавливаем Admin Pack
Запускаем Counter Strike 1.6 сервер.

title: Counter-Strike 1.6 Guide: M4A1 Rifling Techniques, Recoil Theory, Patterns, Control & More
description:
http://WinOut.net In conjunction with CSGoodies we have released a new series exclusively on WinOut.net, Pro Guides, featuring Jame^s who goes over a plethora of facets to competitive Counter-Strike 1.6.

In this installment the veteran leader of teams such as Green Berets, Area 51 and more goes over the topic of the M4A1 and how to properly use it.  Everything you wanted to know about rifling as a CT (or T) with the M4A1 such as proper usage based on different scenarios and variables (i.e. distance from the enemy) to know when to spray, burst or tap is gone over.  Not only this but Jame^s also goes deep into the background of the recoil patterns, the "5th bullet" recoil and much more.

This is a video spanning nearly 14 minutes filled with a plethora of unique information released for FREE courtesy of WinOut.net.

PARTS

* Funny Fail (1): 7:57
* Funny Fail (2): 10:00


General info in-game:

* All models are HD (World views). This for the quality of the game, as the standard models are very undetailed.
* P90, M4A1, M3 shotgun and Aug aren' the original versions, this for the same reason as the first point. (M4A1 is the only one that completely lacks any resemblence of the original one.
* Desert Eagle and grenades are same model but another skin.
* Both CT's and T's packs are different, they are very highly detailed models. Again because of the poor standard quality
* At last, the in-game options are all highest, except for Anti-aliasing, which is x4 instead of x8 for faster performance.


GAMEPLAY MODE: Zombie Escape

* ze stands for Zombie Escape, and is one of the most funniest mods in css that you can find. The game starts with equal teams in T's and CT's and after 8-10 seconds, one player turns into a zombie and must try to hit other players with his single knife... With a bit of luck, he can already hit 3-5 people in a row, and then the epidemy continiues. Otherwise, you have zombie-hunters, which try to kill the first zombie for a quick win (=boring). Zombies have around 2500-3000 health, players the traditional 100hp. Humans must survive to keep the human race alive, otherwise they will be destroyed for an unending life of torment! Have fun!




THANKS TO EVERYONE FOR MAKING THIS VIDEO ONE OF THE MOST POPULAR VIDEOS OF MY CHANNEL, AND FOR MAKING IT THE MOST POPULAR ZOMBIE ESCAPE VIDEO ON YOUTUBE!

~GamingRevenant~

--44 personajes(22 CT y 22 T, incluyendo mujeres y personajes de videojuegos)

-Witch(L4D)
-Charger(L4D2)
-Tank(Jefe)(L4D)
-Boomer(L4D)
-Jocker(l4D2)
-IronMaiden(RE4)
-muchos más
--más de 50 armas
--entre los personajes a elegir destacan:
-Jill Valentine(RE)
-Leon S. Kennedy(RE2)
-Lara Croft(TR)
-Albert Wesker(RE)
-Ada Wong(RE2)
-Zoey(L4D)
-Ellis(L4D2)
-Jack Krauser(RE4)
-Hunk(RE2)
-Los personajes del CSO(Counter Strike Online)
--Voces 100% en español(hombre(vino con un parche)mujer(la de zoey(L4D en español)la de los bots(Ellis o Louis)y la de los rehenes(tambien vino con un parche)

Solo quedan muy pocas cosas para agregar:
-Más armas(quiza)
-Más personajes(quiza)
-Descripcion para los personajes(no todos tienen)
-Agregar plugins
-traducirlo 100% al español(voces y demas)progreso---60%(aprox)

Si deseas colaborar, puedes hacerlo simplemente envia un MP(mensaje privado) con tu aporte(personajes, musica ---muy importante, armas, lo que sea)

Se necesita alguien que quiera hacer una buena imagen de fondo

El juego pesa 2GB(quizas menos) cuando pueda lo subire.

Mañana 08 de Marzo(08/03/11) are otro/s trailer/s y los subire con los 4 mods que faltaron.

-----------
Den ideas!

Por si quieren saber: 
-mi personaje favorito es Ellis(L4D2)
-Modifique la mayoria de los plugins y mods para que queden a mi gusto
-Leere todos los comentarios(pero solo reespondere algunos)
-No volvere a hacer videos que no sean del Counter Strike Project Mx
-Al final no are GTA Project Mx por que ya me aburri y no se puede comparar con el CSPMX
-Tambien se podria llamar(abreviado) CSPMX o CSMX
-No agregare personajes que no sean humanos(me refiero a que sean humanos comunes con las mismas habilidades) como superman o trunks de DBZ(a pesar de ser mi personaje favorito T_T)
-El gordo del final y el zombie que parece de hielo son 2 de los 5 jefes que hay(por ahora).
-Nunca lo are en ingles(o en otro idioma)... a menos que alguien me lo pida xD
-cuando lo grabe pesaba 4 GB y duraba 15 min!!!!(maldito Fraps)
-Todas las canciones son de X-ray Dog, ¿por que? pues por que estan chidas!!
-Soy de uruguay(aunque no creo que a alguien le importe)
-Este... no se que más escribir...
-Comenten...me siento solo xP

---------------- desde que empece este proyecto(2008, si demore bastante xD) siempre quize agregar a Ashley Graham(la del RE4) si alguien la tiene(el skin o model como le digan) por favor digame(y denmelo no?)!!!!!

title: Counter-Strike: Source -- 3rd Person Mod
description: Sloppy gameplay. Point of the video is to show the game in 3rd person mode. All I did was tweak the game using the "cam_ideal" command. It's really buggy, as you can you tell from the muzzle flash and slow-mo running, but it's still pretty fun. The crosshair is useless in 3rd person and can only serve as a reference. You need to aim with the front of the gun, which I've gotten used to. Hence, the reason I aim to the left/right of the crosshair when shooting. I also binded keys to switch between first person and third person on the fly. The game itself is by no means designed to be a third person shooter, but in third person mode it's still alot of fun, especially if you're looking for a third person shooter on PC besides gears or lost planet. Like I said, the game is not gonna be as good 3rd person as an actual 3rd person shooter, but it's a nice change of pace and still pretty fun.

description:
Part 3 of 4.  In September 2010 the Danish national eSports team travelled to Los Angeles U.S.A. to compete in the World Cyber Games -- The olympics of eSports.

After two hectic matches against Brazil and USA, the Danish team reached the final where the best team in world awaited -- Ukraine.

Experience one of the most nail biting finals in Counter Strike history. Niels Thornberg from the national Danish esport association - eSport Danmark, has made a film that contains some of the best highlights from the final. 

The final also contains interviews with two of the players, Danny "Zonic" Sørensen and "Alexander "Ave" Holdt, who comments the development of the match minute by minute, and reflects on thoughts and emotional reactions they had throughout the match.

Playlist: http://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLE6A50F754D876FFD&feature=viewall


* Thanks to this server *
Server: /


** Map info **

You all start in an office, making it for a rush outside, and then the escape has begun. This map is extremely variated, and has some really hot defending moments! Get your way to the tram, and launch the rocket to cure the world from the zombies! Good luck...


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


General info in-game:

* All models are HD (World views). This for the quality of the game, as the standard models are very undetailed.
* P90, M4A1, M3 shotgun and Aug aren' the original versions, this for the same reason as the first point. (M4A1 is the only one that completely lacks any resemblence of the original one.
* Desert Eagle and grenades are same model but another skin.
* Both CT's and T's packs are different, they are very highly detailed models. Again because of the poor standard quality
* At last, the in-game options are all highest, except for Anti-aliasing, which is x4 instead of x8 for faster performance.


GAMEPLAY MODE: Zombie Escape

* ze stands for Zombie Escape, and is one of the most funniest mods in css that you can find. The game starts with equal teams in T's and CT's and after 8-10 seconds, one player turns into a zombie and must try to hit other players with his single knife... With a bit of luck, he can already hit 3-5 people in a row, and then the epidemy continiues. Otherwise, you have zombie-hunters, which try to kill the first zombie for a quick win (=boring). Zombies have around 2500-3000 health, players the traditional 100hp. Humans must survive to keep the human race alive, otherwise they will be destroyed for an unending life of torment! Have fun!
